                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Bosch wanted to enter the automotive aftermarket charging category but faced a critical strategic question: <strong>how to structure a product lineup</strong> that could attract customers at different price points while maximizing shelf space allocation across retail channels. They needed a clear product strategy &mdash; not just a single SKU &mdash; covering entry-level traffic drivers, mid-range volume models, and premium profit generators. The clock was tight: a fixed online marketplace pre-sale date was already scheduled.</p>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase text-sm mb-4 tracking-widest">Our Approach</h3>
                    <div class="bg-green-50/50 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-2xl mb-8">
                        <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">The Solution</p>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">Within <strong>3 days</strong> of the initial briefing, our product and engineering team presented a comprehensive options matrix covering multiple price tiers with differentiated feature sets:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brandOrange font-bold mt-0.5">&rarr;</span> <span><strong>Entry-tier model</strong> &mdash; Essential 30W fast charging at a competitive price point to drive traffic and retail presence</span></li>
