                        <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-red-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">The Challenge</p>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Jacob Jensen, a renowned Danish design house with a rich history in premium watches and industrial design, was making its <strong>first expansion into consumer electronics</strong>. The product concept was audacious: a wireless charging car mount with <strong>dual-sensing automatic opening</strong> &mdash; combining infrared proximity sensing with touch activation for a premium unboxing and daily-use experience. The mechanical challenge: fitting both sensor systems and a reliable arm mechanism into an extremely compact enclosure, a problem multiple suppliers had already failed to solve.</p>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase text-sm mb-4 tracking-widest">Design &amp; Engineering</h3>
                    <div class="bg-green-50/50 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-2xl mb-8">
                        <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">The Solution</p>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Our R&D team redesigned the PCBA layout from the ground up to integrate both sensor systems within the tight enclosure. Through iterative prototyping and precision component placement, we achieved reliable dual-sensing performance &mdash; infrared for hands-free approach detection and capacitive touch for manual control &mdash; without compromising Qi wireless charging efficiency or heat dissipation.</p>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase text-sm mb-4 tracking-widest">Packaging: A Story in Itself</h3>
                    <img src="/image/jacob-jensen-premium-gift-box.webp"
